The only thing that disappointed me was the last of friendliness and enthusiasm of the cashier taking the orders. While people coming from the kitchen greeted the customers, the cashier had the most sour personality. Greet the patrons with a smile, and welcome them into the establishment! Thank them when they pay, and bless them when they leave! If you're having a bad day at least fake it. I'm sure that tip box was pretty much empty today. Anyway, that put a damper on my overall experience, so unfortunately, I had to take a star away. Other than that, the food gets 5 stars! Yummy!!!!!
